Privacy Policy for Chicken Clicker

Effective Date: May 4, 2026

Chicken Clicker is a simple offline tapping game developed by [Developer Name].

This Privacy Policy explains how Chicken Clicker handles user data.

1. Information We Collect

Chicken Clicker does not collect, store, transmit, sell, or share any personal information.

The game does not require:
- Account creation
- Login
- Email address
- Name
- Phone number
- Location
- Camera access
- Microphone access
- Contacts access
- Internet access

2. Local Game Data

Chicken Clicker saves your click count locally on your device so your progress can remain available after closing and reopening the game.

This local save data stays on your device. It is not sent to the developer or to any third party.

You can reset your click count inside the game using the reset option.

3. Children’s Privacy

Chicken Clicker does not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13 or from any other users.

The game is designed to be simple and safe. It does not include ads, in-app purchases, online chat, user accounts, analytics, or external links.

If you believe that personal information has somehow been provided through this game, please contact us so we can investigate and delete it if necessary.

4. Ads and In-App Purchases

Chicken Clicker does not show ads.

Chicken Clicker does not include in-app purchases.

5. Third-Party Services

Chicken Clicker does not use third-party analytics, advertising networks, social media login, or online tracking services.

6. Data Sharing

Chicken Clicker does not share personal data with any companies, organizations, or individuals.

7. Data Security

Since Chicken Clicker does not collect or transmit personal information, no personal information is stored on our servers.

The only game data stored is the local click count saved on your own device.

8. Data Retention and Deletion

Chicken Clicker does not retain personal information.

The local click count remains on your device until:
- You reset it inside the game
- You clear the app’s data through your device settings
- You uninstall the app

